{"word":"H3794 - כִּתִּי - Kittîy - kit-tee' - Chittim","slug":"H3794","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כִּתִּי</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Kittîy"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kit-tee'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Chittim"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05D9;&#x05BC;&#x05D9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05D9; - kitt&#x0131;&#x0302;y  kitt&#x0131;&#x0302;y&#x0131;&#x0302;y</b> - <i>kit-tee', kit-tee-ee'</i><p/>Patrial from an unused name denoting Cyprus (only in the plural); a <i>Kittite</i> or Cypriote; hence an <i>islander</i> in general, that is, the Greeks or Romans on the shores opposite Palestine: - Chittim, Kittim."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3789\">H3789</a>, <a href=\"#/H3791\">H3791</a>, <a href=\"#/H3793\">H3793</a>, <a href=\"#/H4385\">H4385</a>"}]}